CommonFields.Title: High Dielectric Permittivity and Low Percolation Threshold in Nanocomposites Based on Poly(vinylidene fluoride) and Exfoliated Graphite Nanoplates
CommonFields.Author: He, Fuan
Lau, Sienting
Chan, Helen Laiwa
Fan, Jintu
CommonFields.Location: Institute of Textiles and Clothing The Hong Kong Polytechnic University Hung Hom, Kowloon, Hong Kong (China)

Width.description: exfoliated graphite nanoplates with diameters of 0.5-25 micrometer

Length.description: exfoliated graphite nanoplates with diameters of 0.5-25 micrometer

Depth.description: exfoliated graphite nanoplates with thicknesses of 20-60 nm

Mixing.Description: Desired amount of xGnPs was first ultrasonically dispersed in 200 mL of N,N-dimethylformamide (DMF) for 1 hr.
PVDF was added into the xGnP suspension, stirring for 30 min at 80 deg C.

Drying-Evaporation.Description: Poured onto a glass plate to form a thin film and dried at 70 deg C for 3 days.

Dielectric_and_Impedance_Spectroscopy_An.Description: The dielectric porperties of the samples were measured in the frequency range of 50-10^7 Hz at room temperature

Dielectric_Real_Permittivity.description: measured at 1000 Hz and room temperature

data.description: dependence of dielectric constants on the frequency for PVDF/xGnP nano composites at room temperature

Dielectric_Loss_Tangent.description: measured at 1000 Hz and room temperature

ElectricConductivity.description: measured at 1000 Hz and room temperature

data.description: dependence of effective conductivities on the frequency for PVDF/xGnP nanocomposites at room temperature.
